The paper focuses on data and lifecycle management for deep learning, which is a core topic in the field of machine learning. The paper proposes a novel model versioning system and a read-optimized parameter archival storage system, which are relevant to database systems (cs.DB). The paper also conducts experiments on real datasets from computer vision domain, indicating its relevance to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the development of a domain-specific language for deep learning modeling, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). Overall, the paper is most likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category, with cs.DB, cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.SE as secondary categories.
